JUST MIGHT set the pace inside of a vying foe while in the two path around the turn, sparred with that one while shifting to the three path entering the lane, but succumbed in the final furlong and faltered between horses at the sixteenth pole. FOR THE FLAG set the pace along the inside, spun for home in the two path, leaned outwardly a touch while holding sway in midstretch, but drifted out multiple paths entering the final sixteenth, was caught by an outer bidder soon after and fended off outer foes for place while continuing to lug out. SINFILTRE stalked outside of the top pair and in the four path, pressed from the three path around the far turn, attempted a bid turning for home before getting floated back to the four path in upper stretch, brushed with an inner rival while changing leads at the furlong grounds, ran on between horses soon after but was outkicked by an outer rival entering the final sixteenth, sustained her bid for place, but shied from an inner drifting rival and brushed an outer foe approaching the wire while denied place. QUEROBIN DOURADA tracked in the five to three path around the first turn, pursued between horses into the far turn before tucking two wide, swung back to the five path entering the lane, sustained a grinding charge along with an outer foe in the final furlong, got outkicked by that one at the sixteenth pole, kept on in hopes of bidding for show, but took mild contact from an inner rival nearing the wire while missing that position. GLENALL (IRE) stalked along the inside, then chased through the lane while lacking a rail kick. HENRIETTA TOPHAM broke a step slow, settled off of the pace along the inside, got shuffled back behind traffic turning for home to trail at the quarter pole, remained blocked behind foes while off of the rail in midstretch, tipped in and stayed on late. FANCY MARTINI tracked along the inside, tipped to the two path entering the backstretch, but got keen into the far turn, saved ground off of the pace around that bend and made little impact. ARM CANDY broke a beat slow, trailed in the three to five path around the first turn, then raced towards the rear four wide around the far turn before fanning to the seven path entering the lane and moved up. SWEET DANI GIRL pressed two wide, vied around the far turn, then in the three path and between horses in upper stretch, but was herded out by an inner foe causing contact with an outer rival at the furlong grounds, and weakened between horses. LADY HIDEAWAY laid off of the pace in the four to three path, shuffled towards the rear entering the far turn, was held up behind foes nearing the lane, shifted out and failed to menace. PRINCESS THEOREM lacked speed in the four path, lacked a response to urging in the three path and between horses around the far turn and failed to factor. BOUDOIR BURLESQUE steadied from tight quarters among foes entering the first turn, raced off of the pace in the three to four path, gained in the five path entering the far turn, but only managed to chase before getting floated and weakening five to seven wide entering the lane. THE RIDER OF QUEROBIN DOURADA CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST FOR THE FLAG FOR INTERFERENCE IN DEEP STRETCH; BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS.
